<p>
This sounds like a duplicate of <a class="new ticket" href="http://core.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/40522" title="#40522: defect (bug): Twenty Seventeen: Youtube videos are left aligned in Safari (new)">#40522</a>, so I'm going to close it in favour of the original issue.
</p>
<p>
In the meantime, these styles are kind of a modified version of the patch in <a class="new ticket" href="http://core.trac.wordpress.org/ticket/40522" title="#40522: defect (bug): Twenty Seventeen: Youtube videos are left aligned in Safari (new)">#40522</a>. If you copy and paste them into your Custom CSS field, it should knock the video back into place in Safari:
</p>
<pre class="wiki">@supports ( object-fit: cover ) {
    body.has-header-video .custom-header-media iframe {
        -o-object-fit: fill  !important;
        object-fit: fill  !important;
    }
}
</pre><p>
Can you please give that a try, and let me know how it goes?
</p>
